#Create an AWS ec2 instance using console

#1) Choose an Instance Type: Select "t2.micro" This is free-tier eligible.

#2) Configure instance details:
#	*Network: Create a vpc or select default vpc
#	*Auto-assign public IP: Ensure this is "Enable"

#3) Configure security group: This is crucial
#	*Create a new security group.
#	*Add rules:
#		SSH: TYPE:SSH, Source:Myip
#		HTTP: TYPE:HTTP, Source: Anywhere(0.0.0.0/0)
#		HTTPS: TYPE:HTTPS, Source: Anywhere(0.0.0.0/0)

#4) Create keypair:
#	*Create a keypair and Name it
#	*Download the keypair (.pem) file
#       *Launch Insatance

####### Connect to your EC2 Instance ####

# Linux Users
#	*Open terminal and navigate to .pem file location 
#	*Change the file permissions 
		*chmod 400 keypairname.pem
# TO CONNECT:
	*ssh -i keypair.pem ec2-user@public-ip-address-of-your-instance 

#After connecting to ec2, Now downlaod a web Server(APACHE):
	* sudo yum update -y
	
	* sudo yum install -y httpd

	* sudo systemctl start httpd

	* sudo systemctl enable httpd

#Now create a example HTML page:

	* sudo nano /var/www/html/index.html
	
	Now write an example html code in index.html and save 

#Verify your Web server	now
	
#	Open browser and Enter instance public ip into address bar
#	You will see your "html page content"

